<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
5. 
<taxonomicName LSID="64E1E7EA-B4E0-55BC-AD1A-C3D75CC39E96" authority="Welwitsch, Trans. Linn. Soc. London 27: 66 - 70. 1871 = Berlinianche aethiopica (Welw.) Vattimo-Gil" authorityName="Welwitsch, Trans. Linn. Soc. London 27: 66 – 70. 1871 = Berlinianche aethiopica (Welw.) Vattimo-Gil" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pilostyles aethiopica" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aethiopica" status="nom. inval.">Pilostyles aethiopica Welwitsch, Trans. Linn. Soc. London 27: 66-70. 1871 = Berlinianche aethiopica (Welw.) Vattimo-Gil</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="8" pageNumber="49">nom. inval.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bellot &amp; Renner" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="holtzii" status="nom. inval.">Pilostyles holtzii</taxonomicName>
Engler, Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 46: 293. 1912 = 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bellot &amp; Renner" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Berlinianche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="holtzii" status="nom. inval.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinianche holtzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Engl.) Vattimo-Gil, not validly published. Type: Tanzania, Kilimatinde, July 1907, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bellot &amp; Renner" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Berlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="eminii" status="nom. inval.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinia eminii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Taub., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">W. Holtz 1422</emphasis>
(B, destroyed during World War II), 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">syn. nov.</emphasis>
(based on the protologue).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="syntypes">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Syntypes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Angola, Huila, 12 May 1860, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Berlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinia paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Benth. = 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Pseudoberlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Pseudoberlinia paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Benth.) P.A.Duvign., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">F. M. J. Welwitsch 529, 529b</emphasis>
(C, G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Tepals pink to brown, in 3 to 4 whorls each with 3-6 tepals. Male flowers with 1 or 2 ring(s) of ca. 15 pollen sacs, stamen filaments free from the central column (Fig. 6F), hair cushion at the basis of the inner tepals (
<bibRefCitation author="Blarer, A" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" refId="B4" refString="Blarer, A, Nickrent, DL, Endress, PK, 2004. Comparative floral structure and systematics in Apodanthaceae (Rafflesiales). Plant Systematics and Evolution 245: 119-142. doi 10.1007/s00606-003-0090-2." title="Comparative floral structure and systematics in Apodanthaceae (Rafflesiales). Plant Systematics and Evolution 245: 119 - 142. doi 10.1007 / s 00606 - 003 - 0090 - 2" year="2004">Blarer et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Growing in branches of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pellegrin" authorityYear="1943" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Julbernardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Julbernardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Brachystegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Brachystegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, maybe also on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Berlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Berlinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Westia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Westia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Pseudoberlinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Pseudoberlinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in Zimbabwe, Zambia, Tanzania, Angola and Malawi (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Geographic distribution of Apodanthaceae based on label information from 785 herbarium collections." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10621" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Phylogenetic relationships among the hosts of Apodanthaceae (legume relationships from Wojciechowski et al. 2006) and among the species of Apodanthaceae (from Bellot and Renner in review). Identical colors link parasite species and their host (s) and are also used in Figure 2. Dashed lines represent associations with rarely reported hosts; hosts in bold are the most common ones." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10622" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
